how to copy ami from one region to another region?

✅ Steps:
Go to EC2 Dashboard
Click AMIs (left panel)
Select your AMI
Click Actions → Copy AMI
Choose:
Destination region
AMI name
Click Copy AMI

What happens in background
AWS copies associated snapshots from
Amazon Elastic Block Store
Creates a new AMI in target region


how to create snapshot?

✅ Steps:
Go to EC2 Dashboard
Click Volumes
Select the EBS volume
Click Actions → Create Snapshot
Enter:
Description (optional)
Click Create Snapshot

How to create EBS using snapshot?

✅ Steps:
Go to EC2 Dashboard
Click Snapshots
Select your snapshot
Click Actions → Create Volume
Choose:
Availability Zone (must match your Amazon EC2 instance)
Volume type (gp3, io2, etc.)
Size (can increase, not decrease)
Click Create Volume

